# .roadmap.hexa_os_boot mk2 — domain SSOT (owner perspective, origin=hexa-os)
# Header on next line; entries follow as one JSON object per line (mk2 schema).
{"type":"header","kind":"domain","name":"hexa_os_boot","mk":2,"perspective":"owner","origin_repo":"hexa-os","provider_dependency":"hexa-lang:P7-9 fixpoint (@nostd codegen + libc-less ELF emission) + ARM64/x86_64 codegen (UEFI stub linkage) + linker script integration (hexa build flag wiring)","goal":"hexa-os boot domain SSOT: first raw 270 module pair candidate (self/core/boot/ + self/modules/boot/) carrying UEFI stub fn signatures + multiboot2 fallback + Firecracker microVM guest contract — plan-only at this land (compute-bound on upstream)","required_conditions":[{"id":"boot.cond.1","desc":"raw 270 split: self/core/boot/ (fn signatures + types) + self/modules/boot/ (impl) pair created additively","verifier":"test -d self/core/boot && test -d self/modules/boot","status":"unmet","evidence":[],"blocker_reason":"phase.1 of this domain creates these dirs; not yet executed (additive land plan)"},{"id":"boot.cond.2","desc":"raw 271 README.ai.md per group: both self/core/boot/README.ai.md and self/modules/boot/README.ai.md present with frontmatter (schema/last_updated/ssot) + 4 sections (TL;DR, API, Caveats|Failure, File index)","verifier":"hexa run hive/tool/ai_native_module_readme_lint.hexa --root self/core/boot self/modules/boot","status":"unmet","evidence":[],"blocker_reason":"groups not yet created (cond.1 dependency)"},{"id":"boot.cond.3","desc":"UEFI stub fn signature lands: self/core/boot/uefi_stub.hexa declares pub fn uefi_entry(handle: EfiHandle, table: *EfiSystemTable) -> EfiStatus","verifier":"grep -q 'fn uefi_entry' self/core/boot/uefi_stub.hexa","status":"unmet","evidence":[],"blocker_reason":"file not yet authored"},{"id":"boot.cond.4","desc":"Multiboot2 header fallback in self/modules/boot/multiboot2.hexa for legacy BIOS path","verifier":"grep -qE '(MULTIBOOT2_MAGIC|0xe85250d6)' self/modules/boot/multiboot2.hexa","status":"unmet","evidence":[],"blocker_reason":"file not yet authored"},{"id":"boot.cond.5","desc":"Firecracker microVM guest target lands: self/modules/boot/firecracker.hexa with Linux boot protocol header (vmlinux ELF entry + zero-page setup)","verifier":"grep -q 'firecracker_entry' self/modules/boot/firecracker.hexa","status":"unmet","evidence":[],"blocker_reason":"file not yet authored; depends on hexa-lang ELF emission ARM64+x86_64"},{"id":"boot.cond.6","desc":"linker script self/os/linker.ld declares text/data/bss layout for freestanding kernel ELF","verifier":"test -f self/os/linker.ld","status":"unmet","evidence":[],"blocker_reason":"depends on @nostd codegen output format spec from hexa-lang upstream"},{"id":"boot.cond.7","desc":"QEMU smoke test fixture: tool/qemu_boot_smoke.hexa runs hexa-built binary in QEMU and asserts printk hello reached","verifier":"hexa run tool/qemu_boot_smoke.hexa --selftest","status":"unmet","evidence":[],"blocker_reason":"requires actual compilable kernel (depends on cond.3+cond.6); QEMU host tool dependency for test only"},{"id":"boot.cond.8","desc":"freestanding probe (self/os/_freestanding_probe.hexa) preserved byte-identical even after boot module pair lands (additive-only mandate, raw 273)","verifier":"git diff --quiet self/os/_freestanding_probe.hexa","status":"met","evidence":["sha256 94060f9b8d22abb2815bda82a993a51de99752d96bcbc7ceaad094c71dccf6f2 unchanged"],"blocker_reason":""}],"blockers":[{"id":"boot.blk.1","desc":"upstream: hexa-lang P7-9 fixpoint not closed — @nostd codegen + libc-less ELF emission required for any boot stub to compile","type":"upstream","status":"blocked","eta":"","resolution_path":"hexa-lang:.roadmap p7_9_fixpoint cond.* met"},{"id":"boot.blk.2","desc":"upstream: hexa-lang ARM64+x86_64 codegen UEFI calling convention support (System V vs Microsoft ABI for UEFI) — required for cond.3 stub","type":"upstream","status":"blocked","eta":"","resolution_path":"hexa-lang:.roadmap codegen UEFI ABI variant added"},{"id":"boot.blk.3","desc":"upstream: hexa-lang inline asm intrinsic (asm! macro) — required for x86_64 long-mode jump and ARM64 EL switch in boot path","type":"upstream","status":"blocked","eta":"","resolution_path":"hexa-lang:.roadmap codegen ARM64+x86_64 asm! macro RC met"},{"id":"boot.blk.4","desc":"local: linker script authoring decision — UEFI PE-COFF vs ELF for x86_64; ARM64 always ELF","type":"local","status":"design_open","eta":"phase-1","resolution_path":"author self/os/README_BOOT_DESIGN.md (deferred to phase.1 of this domain)"},{"id":"boot.blk.5","desc":"local: QEMU host dependency for cond.7 smoke test — devs need qemu-system-x86_64 / qemu-system-aarch64 installed","type":"local","status":"docs_only","eta":"phase.2","resolution_path":"document in self/modules/boot/README.ai.md File index section"}],"status":"active_plan_only","since":"2026-05-03"}
{"type":"phase","id":"phase.1","name":"Phase 1 — boot pair scaffold (additive only, NO compile)","duration_estimate":"1-2 days","cost_estimate_usd":0,"deliverables":["mkdir self/core/boot/ + self/modules/boot/ (empty dirs)","author self/core/boot/README.ai.md (frontmatter + TL;DR + API stub + Failure modes + File index)","author self/modules/boot/README.ai.md (same shape)","author self/core/boot/uefi_stub.hexa with fn signatures only (no impl, marked TODO)","verify byte-identical: self/os/_freestanding_probe.hexa untouched","run hive/tool/ai_native_module_readme_lint.hexa to confirm conformant"]}
{"type":"phase","id":"phase.2","name":"Phase 2 — implementation lands (after upstream unblocks)","duration_estimate":"3-5 days post-unblock","cost_estimate_usd":0,"deliverables":["self/modules/boot/uefi_stub.hexa impl (calls into hexa_main from probe path)","self/modules/boot/multiboot2.hexa impl with header magic","self/modules/boot/firecracker.hexa impl with Linux boot protocol","self/os/linker.ld linker script","tool/qemu_boot_smoke.hexa golden test","first compile attempt: hexa build self/modules/boot/uefi_stub.hexa --target x86_64-unknown-uefi"]}
{"type":"phase","id":"phase.3","name":"Phase 3 — bench + handoff","duration_estimate":"~1 day","cost_estimate_usd":0,"deliverables":["coldstart measurement on local M-series via QEMU (target <500ms per HEXA_SERVE_V01.md)","emit docs/hexa_os_boot_landed_<date>.ai.md handoff","emit state/markers/hexa_os_boot_landed.marker"]}
{"type":"raw10_caveat","id":"caveat.1","note":"This roadmap is plan-only at this land — no boot dirs created, no boot files authored. Phase.1 execution is the next concrete step but requires user go-ahead per session policy (additive land for plan, not for files)."}
{"type":"raw10_caveat","id":"caveat.2","note":"raw 270 first split candidate is boot (per .roadmap.hexa_os_self_mk2_tuning phase.2 designation). Alternative was law_kernel but boot has shallower upstream dependency (UEFI+linker script vs full law_check trait)."}
{"type":"raw10_caveat","id":"caveat.3","note":"UEFI vs Multiboot2 vs Firecracker are 3 distinct boot paths with different ABI/format requirements. Initial spec covers all 3 stub signatures but only UEFI x86_64 will be the first compiled smoke test (most cloud-relevant per docs/DEPLOYMENT.md matrix)."}
{"type":"raw10_caveat","id":"caveat.4","note":"Firecracker microVM target is significant for hexa-serve v0.1 economics (per HEXA_SERVE_V01.md: 120-500ms unikernel vs 5-30s Linux microVM). cond.5 is the lever for the <500ms coldstart claim."}
{"type":"raw10_caveat","id":"caveat.5","note":"BR-NO-USER-VERBATIM (raw 272) honored: zero /Users/<name>/ paths and zero @-handles in this file. Cross-repo lint dependency (hive/tool/ai_native_module_readme_lint.hexa) referenced relatively (sister-repo path resolved at runtime)."}
{"type":"raw10_caveat","id":"caveat.6","note":"This roadmap supersedes none — it is additive net-new alongside .roadmap.hexa_os_self_mk2_tuning phase.2. The sister roadmap delegated boot pair details here; this roadmap is the detailed contract."}
{"type":"raw10_caveat","id":"caveat.7","note":"Migration explicitly forbidden: the existing self/os/_freestanding_probe.hexa is not relocated to self/modules/boot/. Instead, future boot stub will reference probe entry-point as call target (cross-link, not move)."}
